# Invited talks and conference presentations

K.I. Turk, "Usability, Abusability, and Safety by Design: Tools for Preemptive Prevention of Interpersonal Harms Through Digital Systems." Presented at Paderborn University (8th January 2026) and the University of Erlangen-Nuremberg (19th January 2026).

K.I. Turk and A. Hutchings, ""The Only Gay in the Village": The Experiences of LGBTQ+ Technology-Facilitated Abuse Victims." Presented at the 2nd Gender, Online Safety, and Sexuality Workshop (GOSS) 2025, and the 3rd Cybersecurity and Privacy for Minority and Minoritized People day (CyberMi2) 2025.

L. Hayman, K. Jackson, C. Davidson, L. Parton, K.I. Turk, Panel at European Conference on Domestic Violence (ECDV), September 3-5, 2025, Barcelona, Spain.

K.I. Turk, "Technical Tactics Targeting Tech-Abuse: Tales of AirTag and IoT Misuse." Presented at the University of Edinburgh Controversies in the Data Society, February 14, 2025.

K.I. Turk, "Developing Technical Interventions for Technical Abuse." Presented at the University of Cambridge, October 29, 2024.

T. Shulruff, L.M. Tanczer, K.I. Turk, "Technology-Facilitated Domestic Abuse: Advancements in Its Definition, Scholarship and Response." Panel at European Conference on Domestic Violence (ECDV), September 11-13, 2023, Reykjavik, Iceland.

K.I. Turk, "The failures of anti-stalking protocols in personal item tracking devices." Presented at the IEEE Workshop on Security for Harassment Online, Protections, and Empowerment (SecHOPE), 2023.
